Package com.oracle.coherence.grpc.proxy

The Coherence gRPC server implementation.
Since:
20.06
Author:
Jonathan Knight 2019.11.07
  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    DaemonPoolExecutor.DaemonPoolManagementMBean
    The MBean interface used to register an MBean for the daemon pool.
    NamedCacheClient
    A gRPC NamedCache service.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    CacheRequestHolder<Req,​Res>
    A class that holds a gRPC request, an associated NamedCache and Binary converters.
    CacheRequestHolder.DownConverter
    A Converter that converts from a Binary serialized in one format to a Binary key serialized in a different format.
    CacheRequestHolder.UpConverter
    A Converter that converts from a Binary serialized in one format to a Binary serialized in a different format.
    DaemonPoolExecutor
    An Executor that uses a DaemonPool to execute tasks.
    DaemonPoolExecutor.Builder
    A builder of DaemonPoolExecutor instances.
    DaemonPoolExecutor.DaemonPoolManagement
    The daemon pool MBean.
    NamedCacheService
    A gRPC NamedCache service.
    NamedCacheService.Builder
    A builder that builds instances of NamedCacheService.
    Processors
    A utility class of InvocableMap.EntryProcessor classes used by the NamedCacheService.
    Processors.BaseProcessor<R>
    A base InvocableMap.EntryProcessor.
    Processors.ContainsValueProcessor
    An InvocableMap.EntryProcessor that checks if the mapping for the key exists in the cache.
    Processors.GetProcessor
    An InvocableMap.EntryProcessor that obtains the Binary value mapped to a given key in a cache.
    Processors.ProcessorWithValue<T>
    An InvocableMap.EntryProcessor that contains a value.
    Processors.PutAllProcessor
    An InvocableMap.EntryProcessor that updates the mapping of a number of key to values in a cache.
    Processors.PutIfAbsentProcessor
    An InvocableMap.EntryProcessor that puts the specified value in the cache only if there is no existing mapping for the key.
    Processors.PutProcessor
    An InvocableMap.EntryProcessor that updates the mapping of a key to a value in a cache.
    Processors.RemoveBlindProcessor
    An InvocableMap.EntryProcessor that removes a cache entry without de-serializing keys or values and returns no result.
    Processors.RemoveProcessor
    An InvocableMap.EntryProcessor that obtains the Binary value mapped to a given key in a cache.
    Processors.ReplaceMappingProcessor
    An InvocableMap.EntryProcessor that replaces a specific existing mapping in a cache.
    Processors.ReplaceProcessor
    An InvocableMap.EntryProcessor that replaces an existing mapping in a cache.
